---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Trust Center | BeaconGuard Assurance"
  description="BeaconGuard provides technical control and evidence support at the AI request boundary for regulated enterprise workflows."
>
  <section class="stack-section">
    <h1>Trust Center</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard provides technical control and evidence support at the AI request boundary. It does not create legal compliance guarantees and does not replace an organization's compliance, privacy, security, clinical safety, AML, fraud, SIEM, IAM, or GRC programs.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Evidence Flow</h2>
    <div class="flow-diagram flow-diagram--tight trust-assurance-flow">
      <div class="flow-step">
        <p class="flow-step-title">Policy decision</p>
        <p>Signed metadata, workflow identity, source-system trust, user role, context tags, and policy inputs are evaluated.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <p class="flow-step-title">Record</p>
        <p>Allow, deny, or needs-review outcome is emitted as structured evidence.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <p class="flow-step-title">Review</p>
        <p>Security, privacy, compliance, risk, and audit teams review decision context.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Auditability</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Decision records for allowed, denied, and needs-review outcomes with policy identity.</li>
      <li>Policy identity, request context, approved-pathway status, source-system trust, and result captured at decision time.</li>
      <li>Decision lineage that supports investigation and review without replacing existing systems of record.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Evidence Boundaries</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard provides decision evidence, not model reasoning. It does not claim certainty about model quality, clinical safety, business-logic correctness, or legal compliance status.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Review References</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/sample-decision-record">Review a sample decision record</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/compliance-audit">Compliance and audit</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/overview">Deterministic overview</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/policy-model">Policy identity and replay</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/threat-model">Threat model</a></li>
      <li><a href="/control-responsibility-matrix">Review the control responsibility matrix</a></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/platform">Review platform assumptions</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/contact">Discuss review expectations</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
